Finding Dory A Home!

Dory is extremely playful and terribly sweet. She is also a holy terror - in the best ways possible! Dory is a 2 year-old kitty with Cerebellar Hypoplasia (CH). That means the part of her brain that controls motor function didn't fully develop before she was born.  She's a bit wobbly on her feet and uncoordinated but otherwise healthy and happy. Her condition affects her walking gait - she wobbles a bit. But it doesn't hold her back, and she can run, play, jump and uses her litter box just fine. Dory was born January 29, 2015 in Muscat, Oman. She was adopted then by a great family in Muscat but when they moved and couldn't take her with them, Dory was returned to Muscat Vets to find a new family. On March 30, 2017 Dory flew 8,000 miles to Seattle to find a new family who would spoil her forever.  Upon arrival she went to one of our fabulous foster homes to acclimate to the transition (and learn to meow in English). Dory is a beautiful Oriental Short Hair mix with calico markings. This breed is talkative, active, and does well in homes with children, and lots of activity and stimulation.  Dory loves having her tummy rubbed, likes to lie on her side, (possibly due to her CH) and bat toys around and also loves to carry her toys around in her mouth like prey.  Tonight, Dory was adopted from Denny's Pet World;  her new family is a mother and daughter who saw her online and sought her out at Denny's. Congratulations to Dory's folks for finding their ideal kitty and to Dory for finding her new family and forever home!
